; Module function description  
"<MODULEFUNCTION>" ;<!-- short overview documentation of module function; add reference to detailed information, if available-->
"	<General>	"
"	Engine Controller "
"	</General>	"
""
"	<F1 Name='Read & write IOs' LastModified='04.00.0.0'>"
"	controller for throttle and compressor bypass valve	"
"	</F1>"
"	<F2 Name='Scaling of IOs' LastModified='04.00.0.0'>"
"	 Abstract physical value to the needed raw value of different IO suppliers.	"
"	</F2>"
"	<F3 Name='Filter analog signals' LastModified='04.00.0.0'>"
"	 Filter analog inputs before the were used in the different modules.	"
"	</F3>"
"	<F4 Name='Signal qualitiy check' LastModified='04.00.0.0'>"
"	Check analog input signals if they are in a configured range.	"
"	</F4>"
"	<F5 Name='Hardware monitoring' LastModified='04.00.0.0'>"
"	Check if the hardware configuration maches to the detected IO modules.	"
"	</F5>"
"	<F6 Name='Initiate CAN communication' LastModified='04.00.0.0'>"
"	Initiate CAN interface and start the CAN communication with each CAN device (SAFI, GMU, ...).	"
"	</F6>"
"	<F7 Name='Communication to Multi Measure Devices' LastModified='04.00.0.0'>"
"	Read out asynchron measure data and handle parameter transfer.	"
"	</F7>"
""
